[*] Test: bare function references should trigger "Did you mean /Func?" warnings

/Add [A]: a number, [B]: a number
	[>] [A] + [B]

/Multiply [A]: a number, [B]: a number
	[>] [A] * [B]

/Calculate
[X]: a number, [Y]: a number
	[1] — [R]: Add[ [X], [Y] ]
	[^] WARNING: bare ref to Add — should suggest /Add
	[2] — [S]: Multiply[ [R], [Y] ]
	[^] WARNING: bare ref to Multiply — should suggest /Multiply
	[3] — [T]: /Add[ [R], [S] ]
	[^] OK: proper /Add reference — no warning
	[>] [T]
